<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Our business</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
The Operations MBA Program within Global Consumer &amp; Small Business Banking and Global Technology &amp; Operations gives participants the chance to experience one year rotational assignments in two sub-lines of business within these organizations including but not limited to: Deposits Contact Centers (DCC) and Operations MBA.
<br><br>
<b>Deposits Contact Centers (DCC)</b> provides service and financial solutions to more than 179 million phone customers and 5.1 million email customers each year, making our contact centers among the busiest in the country. In support of the associates servicing our customer's needs, the bank also leverages voice response units (VRU) to answer account inquiries. In 2005, VRUs handled more than 568 million phone calls.
<br><br>
<b>Operations MBA</b> offers processing services for Bank of America customer households and businesses. These services include check processing, statement rendering, cash vault, banking center operations, and lockbox services. Key SFO accomplishments include:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Processing over 8.97 billion checks annually</li>
	<li>Comprising the largest commercial check processor and the largest cash vault system in the world</li>
	<li>Processing over 31 million customer statements monthly</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Overview</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
The Operations MBA Program is a high visibility, graduate, rotational program designed to provide candidates with an opportunity to prepare for future leadership positions in the bank's operational lines of business. Associates participate in 1-year rotational assignments with 2 sub-lines of business within these organizations, including but not limited to Deposits Contact Centers (DCC) and Operations MBA.
</p>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Qualifications</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0;">Education and skills:</p>
<ul>
	<li>MBA degree from an accredited college or university</li>
	<li>3+ years work experience prior to entering graduate school</li>
	<li>Strong leadership and communication skills</li>
	<li>Ability to succeed in a fast-paced collaborative environment</li>
	<li>Excellent organizational and analytical skills</li>
	<li>Ability to understand technology and business requirements</li>
	<li>Ability to learn the organizational structure and the formal/informal workings of the organization</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0;">Personality characteristics:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Strong drive for results</li>
	<li><b>100% geographic flexibility</b></li>
	<li>Team-oriented</li>
	<li>Developed sense of customer and associate satisfaction to drive shareholder value</li>
	<li>Eligibility to work in the United States</li>
</ul>


<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Training</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
The program consists of the following developmental activities and opportunities:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>On-boarding, including orientation and on-going structured events</li>
	<li>Structured learning curriculum (including Six Sigma) and business critical assignments</li>
	<li>Monthly program meetings</li>
	<li>Mentoring and peer coach assignments</li>
	<li>Exposure to senior leadership teams and networking events</li>
</ul>

